WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:02.700
<i> Adult mark: Halloween.</i>

00:02.737 --> 00:04.369
<i> There was no better time</i>
<i> of year for a theatrical boy</i>

00:04.405 --> 00:06.238
<i> Than one that mandated</i>
<i> costumes.</i>

00:06.307 --> 00:07.840
[chalk thumps]

00:07.842 --> 00:10.042
- Now, who can tell me

00:10.044 --> 00:12.143
What important day is upon us?

00:13.180 --> 00:15.180
Mm.
- Halloween!

00:15.216 --> 00:16.915
It's gonna be awesome.

00:17.051 --> 00:18.716
<i> I'm sleeping over</i>
<i> at ritchie's.</i>

00:18.753 --> 00:20.885
[students laugh]

00:22.923 --> 00:24.923
[spooky slow Halloween
music plays]

00:26.059 --> 00:28.193
- I was referring
to all saint's day.

00:28.195 --> 00:29.795
- We're in grade seven!

00:29.864 --> 00:31.530
Halloween is for
kindergarten babies.

00:31.532 --> 00:33.265
- But Halloween's fun.

00:33.334 --> 00:35.867
Zombies, witches, ghosts.

00:35.936 --> 00:38.136
- The only ghost you should
concern yourself with

00:38.271 --> 00:39.971
Is the holy one.

00:40.041 --> 00:42.741
<i>And the only 'zombie' I know of</i>
<i> is lazarus,</i>

00:42.876 --> 00:45.510
Whom christ himself raised
from the dead.

00:46.847 --> 00:49.415
- Uh, I think what sister rose
is trying to say, children,

00:49.550 --> 00:51.283
Is there's nothing
to be afraid of.

00:51.418 --> 00:54.019
- Yes, sister.
When you die, children,

00:54.088 --> 00:56.988
<i> There are only two possible</i>
<i> destinations:</i>

00:57.058 --> 00:59.357
The eternal light of heaven

00:59.427 --> 01:01.893
Or the eternal flames of hell.

01:03.097 --> 01:05.163
[students murmur nervously]

01:06.500 --> 01:08.233
<i> Adult mark: Who needed dracula</i>
<i> to give you nightmares</i>

01:08.269 --> 01:10.235
<i> When you had nuns.</i>

01:10.237 --> 01:13.238
♪♪♪

01:13.240 --> 01:14.907
[low hum of chatter]

01:14.909 --> 01:16.641
Ritchie: What am I gonna do
with my costume now?

01:16.710 --> 01:18.377
Mark: What do you mean?
You're gonna wear it.

01:18.512 --> 01:20.178
Who cares what they think?

01:20.247 --> 01:22.347
- Me. Like, a lot.

01:23.951 --> 01:25.383
- Gimme some.

01:25.453 --> 01:27.785
- Isn't begging for junk food
for "kindergarten babies?"

01:27.922 --> 01:30.856
- But this could be our last
year trick-or-treating.

01:30.925 --> 01:32.223
Come with us.

01:32.259 --> 01:34.460
- I guess I could go for a bit.

01:34.595 --> 01:36.395
I don't have a costume,
and I'd need a mask -

01:37.565 --> 01:39.464
So nobody sees me with you.

01:39.467 --> 01:42.801
- They have chocolate bars
as big as dogs on my street.

01:44.071 --> 01:46.271
- Okay, okay, I'm in.

01:46.273 --> 01:48.874
[chip bag rustles]

01:48.943 --> 01:51.076
- [chips crunch loudly]
in for what?

01:51.078 --> 01:52.844
- She's coming trick
or treating with us.

01:52.913 --> 01:55.280
- [snickers]
you are, are ya?

01:55.349 --> 01:57.248
You taking yer sooky bottle too?

01:57.284 --> 01:59.017
[chair scrapes back]
- frig off!

01:59.153 --> 02:00.686
I never said I was going
with them.

02:00.821 --> 02:02.554
Follow them and take
all their candy.

02:02.689 --> 02:04.422
- Wait. Let me get this
straight.

02:04.492 --> 02:06.824
You're gonna follow us
house to house,

02:06.861 --> 02:08.960
But instead of taking
free candy,

02:08.996 --> 02:11.029
You're gonna steal ours?

02:11.031 --> 02:12.497
- Exactly.

02:12.500 --> 02:14.500
- I rescind my invitation.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.702
<i> [students chuckle nearby]</i>

02:16.704 --> 02:18.570
- Watch your backs tonight,
dicks.

02:18.639 --> 02:20.104
[light thump]

02:20.141 --> 02:21.773
- [snickering] dicks.
- [whispers] sorry.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.379
- I don't wanna go anymore.

02:27.448 --> 02:29.247
- New strategy.

02:29.316 --> 02:31.250
We trick-or-treat by my house.

02:31.385 --> 02:33.619
No way the foxes can get to us
out there.

02:33.754 --> 02:36.788
- [snorts] no offense,
but there aren't any houses.

02:36.790 --> 02:38.490
- Pffft!

02:38.559 --> 02:41.360
I have my sources.

02:41.362 --> 02:43.595
[creepy organ music plays]

02:45.032 --> 02:47.666
- Shockin'! This spider's seen
better days!

02:47.668 --> 02:50.202
- Mm. Well, it's still got
two good legs

02:50.337 --> 02:52.538
And an arse full of web.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.806
Mm. Sounds a bit like myself.

02:54.808 --> 02:57.442
I'm a bit more worried
about the candy.

02:57.444 --> 02:59.945
We're down to our last
couple of fistfuls.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.447
- Oh, well, I wonder why
that is, ya greedy bugger!

03:02.516 --> 03:04.483
Leave some for the kids.
Mike jr.: What kids?

03:04.485 --> 03:06.351
Nobody ever comes trick
or treatin' out here.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.820
- That's right!
Waste not, want not!

03:08.822 --> 03:10.422
[door clicks shut]

03:10.557 --> 03:12.890
[laughing, footsteps tap
across the floor]

03:12.927 --> 03:14.760
- Oh! Let's get a look at you,
boys.

03:14.895 --> 03:16.361
<i> Pop: Oh, ho-ho-ho!</i>

03:16.363 --> 03:18.430
<i> Adult mark: Ah, the plastic</i>
<i> smock costumes</i>

03:18.565 --> 03:20.365
<i> Of '80s childhood!</i>

03:20.367 --> 03:22.334
<i>I couldn't wait to show it off.</i>

03:22.403 --> 03:24.536
- Oh, you'll freeze
your arse off!

03:24.538 --> 03:26.004
- Wha-- [frustrated sigh]

03:26.139 --> 03:27.406
[hangers clatter]

03:27.408 --> 03:29.274
- Mom! Nobody'll see
our costumes!

03:29.409 --> 03:31.643
- That wind'll cut you
in half.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.712
[jacket rustles]
here.

03:33.714 --> 03:35.714
Put that on!

03:35.716 --> 03:37.583
You be careful out
on that road.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.917
We live on a four-lane highway,
for god's sake.

03:39.954 --> 03:41.587
Imagine your mother's face

03:41.722 --> 03:44.055
If we sent you home
looking like roadkill, hmm?

03:45.125 --> 03:46.691
- You think we can get
run over?

03:46.727 --> 03:48.493
- No!
- Absolutely.

03:49.563 --> 03:51.029
Pop: [gleeful] it's the fairies.

03:51.164 --> 03:53.932
They're a real danger
on days like this.

03:53.934 --> 03:55.534
<i> Adult mark: Some of the old</i>
<i> folks still believed</i>

03:55.536 --> 03:57.535
<i> In the old irish folktales</i>

03:57.571 --> 04:00.138
<i> Of the 'little people'</i>
<i> who lived in the woods.</i>

04:00.207 --> 04:03.074
<i> - The fairies get mad</i>
<i> on all soul's night.</i>

04:03.143 --> 04:04.509
Mike jr.: Ah, here he goes.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.511
- Oh no, it's all right,
you can laugh all you want,

04:06.513 --> 04:07.980
But it's true.

04:08.115 --> 04:10.749
And stay outta those woods
or they'll run after ya.

04:10.751 --> 04:12.617
<i> And disguising yourself</i>
<i> as one of them,</i>

04:12.620 --> 04:14.319
<i> That's not gonna help.</i>

04:14.454 --> 04:16.387
- We're smurfs.

04:17.691 --> 04:20.391
- Here. Put this bread
in your pocket.

04:20.427 --> 04:22.627
[jacket rustles]
and you, too.

04:22.663 --> 04:24.362
Nah-uh. Come on.

04:24.431 --> 04:27.365
- Why do we need bread
when we're getting candy?

04:27.434 --> 04:29.768
- It's not for you, laddie.

04:29.770 --> 04:31.402
It's for the fairies.

04:32.572 --> 04:35.606
Many a child has gone missing
in those woods.

04:38.845 --> 04:40.978
<i> Mary: [laughing] give it up,</i>
<i> pop.</i>

04:41.015 --> 04:43.114
<i> You're scarin' him.</i>
<i> - [chuckles gleefully]</i>

04:43.183 --> 04:44.449
- Never you mind.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.318
The only thing you have
to worry about

04:46.320 --> 04:48.520
Is some sick bastard putting
razor blades in your candy.

04:48.589 --> 04:50.121
Or a car pulling up

04:50.190 --> 04:51.923
And snatching you off
to god knows where.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.391
<i> Adult mark: Mom had a way</i>
<i> of comforting you</i>

04:53.460 --> 04:55.793
<i> That somehow made</i>
<i> everything worse.</i>

04:55.929 --> 04:58.262
- Oh, people are sick
these days, I tell ya.

04:58.299 --> 05:00.098
Sick!
[pop chuckles]

05:00.100 --> 05:02.333
- M-maybe we should go
to my house.

05:02.335 --> 05:05.503
- Oh, pop, you've got this
youngster scared to death!

05:06.774 --> 05:08.874
- Well, you never know what's
waiting for you out there

05:09.009 --> 05:11.409
In the cold, dark night.

05:13.714 --> 05:16.013
- [yells] jesus murphy!
- What?

05:16.050 --> 05:18.083
<i> - [screams] ohhh! No!</i>

05:18.152 --> 05:19.584
- Is that fairies?

05:19.620 --> 05:21.452
- Oh, it's just a big,
bloody ol' moose!

05:21.488 --> 05:23.622
Oh, you... You dirty big bugger!
Get!

05:23.757 --> 05:25.289
Get outta here!

05:25.326 --> 05:27.158
<i> Adult mark: Some people had</i>
<i> to deal with stray cats.</i>

05:27.194 --> 05:29.294
<i> Where we lived,</i>
<i> it was stray moose.</i>

05:29.429 --> 05:31.096
[door squeaks open,
pot clanks]

05:32.766 --> 05:35.200
- Go on now, before I put your
head on the wall, ya bastard!

05:35.335 --> 05:38.169
- Get! Oh, you big dumb moose,
get outta here!

05:38.238 --> 05:39.571
[pot clanks, pop yells]
- oh.

05:39.640 --> 05:41.939
- So, what do you say?
Wanna go trick-or-treating?

05:41.975 --> 05:43.742
<i> Mary: Oh! Go on! Go away!</i>

05:45.211 --> 05:47.445
[pot clanks]
get, get, get, get! Oh...

05:47.514 --> 05:49.180
[pot clanks]

05:49.216 --> 05:50.849
- Ah, asshole.

05:52.252 --> 05:53.985
[door slams shut]

05:54.054 --> 05:55.721
<i> Adult mark: Most kids trick-or</i>
<i> treated on their street,</i>

05:55.856 --> 05:58.523
<i> But my street was</i>
<i> the trans-canada highway.</i>

05:58.525 --> 06:00.658
[car rumbles past]
ritchie: That one felt close.

06:00.660 --> 06:03.728
Didn't it feel close?
- Would ya relax?

06:03.731 --> 06:05.664
There's nothing
to be scared of.

06:05.799 --> 06:07.733
<i> [loud rumble, horn honks]</i>

06:07.868 --> 06:10.368
[blazer rumbles to a halt,
gearshift clunks]

06:11.572 --> 06:13.939
- Evenin', boys. Need a lift?

06:14.074 --> 06:15.607
- We're okay, dad.

06:16.910 --> 06:19.677
- Is this the pumpkin patrol?
Cool!

06:19.747 --> 06:21.746
<i> Adult mark: Each year,</i>
<i> dad and dick drove around</i>

06:21.749 --> 06:24.515
<i> Passing out treats and keeping</i>
<i> kids safe from everything</i>

06:24.551 --> 06:26.685
<i> Except type 2 diabetes.</i>

06:26.820 --> 06:28.352
Dick: That's right.

06:28.389 --> 06:30.688
Vocm, coming at you, live,
all night,

06:30.724 --> 06:32.891
Keeping the ghosts
and goblins safe!

06:32.893 --> 06:34.493
Arrive alive!

06:34.628 --> 06:37.095
[ritchie gasps,
bag rustles and thumps]

06:37.230 --> 06:38.596
- Ow...
- Great costumes.

06:39.767 --> 06:41.466
You guys a couple
of blueberries?

06:41.601 --> 06:43.367
- We're smurfs.

06:43.404 --> 06:45.236
- I'm a sexy fireman!

06:45.272 --> 06:46.771
- Dick! Youngsters!

06:46.807 --> 06:48.907
- I mean, I'm a fireman.

06:48.976 --> 06:50.909
<i> Mike sr.: You sure you boys</i>
<i> are all right?</i>

06:50.911 --> 06:53.244
- We are fine, dad!

06:53.280 --> 06:55.913
- I know, I know. It's just
your mother was worried is all.

06:56.983 --> 06:58.784
- Gotta go, mike.
We got candy to give out!

06:58.919 --> 07:00.384
- Here. Pick me up a pack
of smokes

07:00.421 --> 07:02.019
When you get
to the gas station!

07:02.055 --> 07:04.189
[gearshift clunks,
blazer rumbles away]

07:04.258 --> 07:06.324
<i> Adult mark: Smokes money from</i>
<i>dad wasn't technically a treat,</i>

07:06.326 --> 07:08.226
<i> But it was a start.</i>

07:09.663 --> 07:11.562
- Now, ye crowd behave
yourselves

07:11.598 --> 07:13.397
While I'm taking your
little brother out!

07:13.434 --> 07:15.099
If there's any trouble,
I'll be shipping ya off

07:15.169 --> 07:16.801
To your father's. I mean it!

07:17.871 --> 07:20.004
- Frig off, ya sooky babies!

07:20.073 --> 07:21.873
- Oh, stop it! Tsk, tsk, tsk!

07:22.008 --> 07:23.608
You taught him that,
didn't ya?!

07:23.610 --> 07:26.010
[car rumbles away]
[snickering]

07:26.012 --> 07:28.412
- Guys! You heard her.

07:28.449 --> 07:30.282
If you wanna start staying
at mom's house more,

07:30.284 --> 07:31.817
You better listen.

07:31.952 --> 07:34.486
- Trick or treat?
I says "trick!"

07:34.488 --> 07:37.088
[footsteps thud]

07:37.090 --> 07:38.657
[hard whack]

07:38.792 --> 07:40.892
<i> Brothers: [laugh]</i>

07:43.463 --> 07:45.263
<i> Adult mark: It's tough trick</i>
<i> or-treating at your neighbours</i>

07:45.332 --> 07:47.798
<i> When your closest neighbour</i>
<i> is a car lot.</i>

07:47.835 --> 07:50.234
Boys: Trick or treat!
- What do we got here?

07:50.270 --> 07:52.169
A couple of woodland fairies?

07:52.206 --> 07:53.905
Mark: Something like that.

07:53.941 --> 07:56.708
Wacky wesley: Uh, well, okay.
Th-this is a car lot.

07:56.777 --> 07:59.444
I wasn't exactly ready for
trick-or-treaters.

08:00.514 --> 08:01.846
Ah! There we go!

08:02.916 --> 08:05.450
- Certs.
Oh, and cough drops!

08:05.585 --> 08:07.118
Good!

08:07.120 --> 08:09.387
You know, I was starting to get
a little tickle in my throat.

08:09.522 --> 08:11.088
Score!

08:13.660 --> 08:16.528
- Don't eat 'em all at once,
boys.

08:16.530 --> 08:19.363
[spooky music plays]

08:20.667 --> 08:22.400
[footsteps trudge]

08:22.402 --> 08:23.968
- An air freshener,

08:25.205 --> 08:27.405
Double a batteries,

08:29.409 --> 08:31.676
A free tire rotation
with every oil

08:31.678 --> 08:33.811
And filter change.

08:35.115 --> 08:37.282
- It's all year round. Good,
they finally changed that.

08:37.351 --> 08:39.383
<i> [crow caws in the distance]</i>

08:40.921 --> 08:42.954
- Should we just go home?

08:42.990 --> 08:45.222
Maybe we are too old
for Halloween,

08:46.260 --> 08:48.326
'cause this sucks.

08:49.429 --> 08:50.828
[crow caws in the distance]

08:50.864 --> 08:52.830
- Okay, let's go.

08:54.434 --> 08:56.367
I know a shortcut.

08:56.403 --> 08:58.102
- What about the fairies?

08:58.171 --> 09:00.638
- Fairies aren't real.
Kidnappers are though.

09:00.707 --> 09:02.807
[spooky music plays]

09:04.778 --> 09:07.045
[crow caws,
distant scream]

09:08.715 --> 09:10.715
<i> Adult mark: We were down</i>
<i> in the dumps,</i>

09:10.717 --> 09:13.051
<i> So why not take a shortcut</i>
<i> through the dump?</i>

09:13.053 --> 09:16.254
♪♪♪

09:16.389 --> 09:18.255
<i> The ol' dump in the woods</i>
<i> was where things went</i>

09:18.292 --> 09:20.191
<i> Before the environment</i>
<i> was invented.</i>

09:20.327 --> 09:22.226
Ritchie: [whispers] mark.
Mark: [laboured breathing]

09:22.296 --> 09:24.362
[car idles]

09:24.364 --> 09:26.264
<i>Adult mark: Everything ended up</i>
<i> there -</i>

09:26.266 --> 09:28.133
<i> Cars, refrigerators -</i>

09:29.536 --> 09:31.870
<i> But I had never seen anyone</i>
<i> dump a body there before.</i>

09:31.872 --> 09:33.771
Ritchie: [screams] oh my god!

09:33.773 --> 09:36.541
[rug thumps]

09:36.543 --> 09:38.009
Boys: [gasp]

09:38.078 --> 09:39.811
[tense music plays]

09:39.813 --> 09:41.879
[footsteps crunch]

09:44.818 --> 09:46.685
Man: Oh jesus! Fairies!
Boys: [screaming]

09:46.820 --> 09:49.153
Men: [screaming]

09:49.155 --> 09:50.855
All: [screaming in terror]

09:52.459 --> 09:54.092
<i>Adult mark: You know you live</i>
<i> in the boonies</i>

09:54.094 --> 09:55.760
<i> When people feel comfortable</i>
<i> dropping a dead body</i>

09:55.762 --> 09:56.895
<i> Next to your house.</i>

09:59.600 --> 10:01.232
<i> Door handle rattles]</i>

10:01.301 --> 10:03.301
[knocking at the door,
door handle rattles]

10:03.436 --> 10:05.036
- Oh, we got some kids!
[mary laughs excitedly]

10:05.038 --> 10:06.471
[door clicks open]

10:06.606 --> 10:07.772
[running footsteps,
door bangs shut]

10:07.774 --> 10:09.641
<i>Mike jr.: No, it's just them.</i>
<i> Told ya!</i>

10:09.776 --> 10:12.377
- Aw, look at 'em all worn out.
How was your night?

10:12.446 --> 10:14.245
- [wheezing] dead... Body...

10:15.448 --> 10:18.216
- So... Much... Blood.

10:18.218 --> 10:20.652
- What're you talking about?

10:20.787 --> 10:24.656
- We... We saw someone
to-tossing a dead body

10:24.791 --> 10:26.524
In... In the dump!

10:26.560 --> 10:28.393
- Oh, come off it.
They're lying.

10:28.462 --> 10:30.428
- We did! Honest!

10:31.565 --> 10:33.331
<i> [wolf howls on tv]</i>

10:33.466 --> 10:35.566
- Do you boys swear
you're telling the truth?

10:36.936 --> 10:39.204
<i> Adult mark: Finally, someone</i>
<i> was taking us seriously.</i>

10:39.339 --> 10:40.805
<i> [glass shatters,</i>
<i> woman screams on tv]</i>

10:40.807 --> 10:42.740
- [triumphantly] I knew it!

10:42.876 --> 10:44.676
I said something terrible
would happen tonight,

10:44.811 --> 10:47.078
And it did! I was right!
[laughs gleefully]

10:47.147 --> 10:48.813
Boys: [breathing hard]

10:48.948 --> 10:51.249
- Oh, but I'm glad that
you boys are safe though.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.218
Yeah, that's good.

10:54.287 --> 10:56.354
[chainsaw buzzes on tv,
boys catch their breath]

10:57.991 --> 10:59.691
[hard whack,
plastic bones scatter]

10:59.826 --> 11:01.759
Brothers: [laughing gleefully]

11:01.795 --> 11:04.562
[dog barks nearby,
brothers sigh]

11:05.832 --> 11:07.765
<i> Adult mark: Fox may not have</i>
<i> outgrown Halloween,</i>

11:07.767 --> 11:09.067
<i> But she had outgrown</i>
<i> her brothers.</i>

11:09.202 --> 11:11.302
[kids chatter,
brothers chortle]

11:11.338 --> 11:12.970
- Wait!

11:13.006 --> 11:15.440
Leave 'em alone.
I'll tell mom.

11:15.509 --> 11:17.842
- You'd love to have us shipped
off to dad's, wouldn't you?

11:17.977 --> 11:19.910
- She thinks she's too good
for us.

11:19.946 --> 11:22.146
- I'm here with you now,
aren't I?

11:22.182 --> 11:23.781
- Here, then.
[bat clatters]

11:25.152 --> 11:28.953
These have been out in the sun
for 3 weeks.

11:28.989 --> 11:32.423
- Ha! Gross! Chicken poo!
[moronic laugh]

11:32.459 --> 11:34.658
- This place looks like it
could use a little stinking up.

11:36.229 --> 11:38.796
<i> [kids laugh and chatter</i>
<i> in the distance]</i>

11:40.133 --> 11:41.733
